PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1773338768
OL,3,CPeople warned to avoid reliance on
OL,4,Cdrugs like ibuprofen for pain relief
OL,6,F"Although NSAIDs, such as ibuprofen,
OL,7,Fare effective and safe medicines,
OL,8,Fpatients should be aware of their
OL,9,Fimpact ` particularly if a patient is
OL,10,Fat increased risk of developing kidney
OL,11,Fdisease ` and consider alternative
OL,12,Fmedication where appropriate.
OL,14,F"If a patient has concerns about their
OL,15,Fusage of NSAIDs, they should speak to
OL,16,Ftheir pharmacist who can advise them."
OL,18,FAround 7.2 million people in the UK
OL,19,Fare living with some form of chronic
OL,20,Fkidney disease, which usually has no
OL,21,Fsymptoms in the early stages.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
